# Catalog of toggleable external agents that the agent_network_designer can call after step 1.
#
# Each entry is gated by an environment variable. When the env var is set to a truthy value
# ("1", "true", "yes", "on" — case-insensitive), ExternalAgentsMiddleware (a) appends the
# entry's `instructions` text to the designer's system prompt and (b) keeps the entry's `tool`
# in the model request's tools list. When the env var is unset/falsy, the middleware strips
# the tool from `ModelRequest.tools` before the model call so the LLM literally can't invoke
# it — the static declaration in the designer HOCON is only the upper bound; this catalog is
# the gate.
#
# Fields:
#   enabled_env_var: name of the env var that toggles this module on/off.
#   tool:            tool reference (e.g. "/middleware_manager"). Must match the tool name as
#                    it appears in the designer's `tools` list. Used to filter ModelRequest.tools.
#   instructions:    workflow-step text appended to the designer's system prompt when enabled.

{
    "middleware_manager": {
        "enabled_env_var": "AGENT_NETWORK_DESIGNER_USE_MIDDLEWARE",
        "tool": "/middleware_manager",
        "instructions": """
- `/middleware_manager`: Delegate attaching or removing agent-level middleware to the
  middleware_manager subnetwork.

  About middleware
  A middleware is a reusable behavior layer attached per LLM agent (function / coded-tool
  agents have no model call to intercept). It runs on every model call to that agent and can
  redact PII in inputs/outputs, inject a checklist or skill catalog into the system prompt,
  enforce guardrails, log decisions for audit, etc. The catalog of available middleware
  classes lives inside the middleware_manager — you don't need to pick the class
  yourself; describe the network's compliance / behavior needs and let it choose. Attached
  middleware is stored on each agent's `middleware` array and persisted with the network.

  When to invoke
  - The user explicitly asks for middleware, or for a behavior layer on any agent.
  - The network includes LLM agents whose responsibilities suggest a behavior layer would
    add value. Defer to the middleware_manager — it sees the current catalog and
    will decide whether an applicable middleware exists.

  When NOT to invoke
  - No behavior-layer concern applies and the user did not ask for middleware.
  - Every agent in the network is a function / coded-tool agent (no model call to wrap).
"""
    },
}
